1
00:00:00,087 --> 00:00:02,438
JavaScript classes support inheritance

2
00:00:02,663 --> 00:00:05,612
which allows one class to extend another class

3
00:00:06,013 --> 00:00:11,900
This means that you can create a new class that inherits the properties and methods of an existing class

4
00:00:12,287 --> 00:00:16,875
and you can add or override existing functionality to suit specific needs

5
00:00:17,262 --> 00:00:21,788
Inheritance in JavaScript is implemented using the `extends` keyword

